com.j2bugzilla.base

Class AttachmentFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.j2bugzilla.base.AttachmentFactory

  • public class AttachmentFactory
extends Object
    The AttachmentFactory is responsible for creating new Attachment objects based off of data from either a Bugzilla installation or user input. It is responsible for determining the correct Attachment subtype to instantiate.
    Author:
    Tom

      • newAttachment

        public AttachmentFactory newAttachment()
        Tells the AttachmentFactory to begin building a new Attachment. This method must be called before any of the set methods, and before createAttachment().
        Returns:
        A reference to the current factory, so that invocations can be chained fluently.
